UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387894000069
KW  - UN System of National Accounts
AB  - The recent revision of the United Nations System of National Accounts (SNA) represents improved harmonization of the international trade, balance of payments, government finance and monetary data collected by national and international statistical agencies. Although such harmonization is welcomed by the developing countries, a number of other major unresolved issues remain. Specifically, the SNA has not solved problems relating to (1) delineation of the formal and informal sectors of an economy, (2) appropriate treatment of market and non-market production, and (3) satisfactory analysis of sector saving and capital formation and (4) harmonization of household sector macrodata with household survey microdata.
ER  - 

